   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE SECOND STEP OF GOD'S SALVATION IN LIFE TRANSFORMATION Scripture Reading: 2 Cor 3:18; Rom 12:2a OUTLINE The definition of transformation: Not merely a perceptible change outwardly in behavior.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Being a metabolic transformation inwardly in essence.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The steps of transformation: Washing the washing of regeneration Titus 3:5b.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Sanctification the sanctification of the Holy Spirit Rom 6:19, 22; 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Renewing the renewing of the Holy Spirit Titus 3:5b: Beginning from our mind Rom 12:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Through our spirit, which is mingled with the Spirit Eph 4:23; Rom 8:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Reaching all the inward parts of our being.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A metabolic process transformation Rom 12:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Not accomplished in an instant.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>But achieved throughout our entire life 2 Cor 4:16-17.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The way of transformation: By fellowshipping with the Lord without any barrier with unveiled face beholding and reflecting like a mirror the glorious image of the Lord 3:18a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The advancing from one degree of glory to another degree of glory v. 18b.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Being transformed into the same image of the Lord, even as from the Lord Spirit v. 18c.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>By remaining in our spirit and exercising our spirit 2 Tim 4:22; Phil 4:23; Gal 6:18.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The issue of transformation: Growth and maturity in the divine life Eph 4:13b; Col 1:28.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Arriving at the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ Eph 4:13c.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The purpose of transformation: The building up of the Body of Christ v. 12.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The accomplishing of God's eternal economy 3:9.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The ultimate transformation: The transfiguration of our body Phil 3:21.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The glorification of our body Rom 8:30.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The ultimate redemption v. 23c; Eph 1:14; 4:30.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The full taste of the divine sonship Rom 8:23b.</S>
   </TEXT>
